On Wed, 22 Jan 2003, Dean Landi wrote:

> 1)    I was just wondering how much damage I did when I snapped off one
> of the bolts while tighting down the drivers side CV joints.

Not a problem.  Just take the axle off and the remaining part of the bolt
should turn right out.  If you broke it flush, you might be able to get
some purchase on the back side of the flange with needle nose pliers.

